Rating: 0
Rarely do I comment on recipes, but this one earned a comment or two. These meatballs are Outstanding! Couple of suggestions based on making this recipe about 10 times so far: 1) Must add the currants and even more than is called for; same with the pine nuts. Try 3T each. You will be rewarded with extra sweetness and flavor. 2) These can be made with both Italian Sausage and a Beef/Pork/Veal meatloaf mixture and both versions are excellent. I have decided to make these with the BPV mixture because it makes handling and mixing easier. 3) You can cheat by using 1/2 cup Seasoned Italian breadcrumbs. As others have said, these meatballs freeze well. I have kept them for up to a month with no apparent degradation in taste. Finally, I make my own sauce and like others didn't like this simple sauce.

