Don't be fooled by the 3 fork rating--I only give 4 forks if I am completely overwhelmed by a dish's deliciousness. I thought that these meatballs were excellent, and I will definitely make them again. The amount of breadcrumbs does seem like a lot, but it works well since these meatballs are all sausage. If you used less breadcrumbs, you would just be eating a fatty sausage ball. I loved the pine nuts and would definitely add them next time. As for the currants, I substituted golden raisins per another reviewer's suggestion because I had tons of them in the pantry. I liked the raisins, but my boyfriend's reaction was more ambivalent for textural reasons. Next time I think that I'll probably use half the amount of raisins, and I'll maybe cut them in an even finer dice than I did this time. I added oregano, a bay leaf, and red pepper flakes to my sauce and it turned out just fine. So you could either do that or substitute your own sauce. I think that the original recipe is going for authentic simplicity, but I can see why some people thought that it was boring.

