Awesome recipe. After reading all the rave reviews, I used a lb of ground beef and a lb of sausage and froze half the meatballs for another time. I always bake my meatballs and recommend using a wire rack over the pan so that the fat can drip off. Believe me, they will get brown! To those who suggested the bread crumbs were in excess, absolutely not! I learned how to make meatballs from a great Italian cook many years ago and he advised that roughly a third of the mix should be breadcrumbs. This helps to keep them moist and firm. I was not even sure what pine nuts were, let alone how to toast them! For those who might be wondering, you toss them in a dry skillet over medium heat until browned. My husband does not like to try new things and swears that he does not like nuts (no allergy), so I chopped the pine nuts and currants finely. He loved this dish, as did I!

