Love this recipe with a few modifications. Based on other reviewers' comments, I make the "Spicy Tomato Sauce" on this site (punched up with extra spices). I also double the amount of currants and pine nuts, which are really what make these meatballs special. Also, instead of heating the meatballs in the sauce, I warm them in the oven and add them to the sauce just before serving. (The meatballs soak up way too much salt if heated up in the sauce as the recipe calls for.) The "sweetness" of the meatballs, combined with the spiciness of the tomato sauce make of a truly wonderful (and relatively easy) meal. Double the ingredients and have leftovers to freeze!

