Rating: 2
These meatballs were OK, but... Here's how to make great meatballs: mix the following in a bowl: 1 lb. ground beef (10% fat), water-soaked stale italian bread (about 3-4 one inch slices, press out excess water), 1/2 cup grated parmigianno cheese, 1/4 tsp. grated nutmeg, 2 Tbs. granulated garlic powder, fresh parsley, 1/2 cup pine nuts (pignoli), 1 large whole egg, salt/pepper (lots of pepper). Here's the real trick: before you fry them in about 1/2 inch of olive oil, roll the raw meatballs (about the size of a golf ball) around in flavored bread crumbs!(I use 4C) Then fry until golden brown and place on paper towel to drain. I guarantee they will be the best meatballs you've ever tasted!

